<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,258,1434]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1229,1253]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is probably a close ally to 
<taxonomicName box="[754,870,1230,1253]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pagaronia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="protecta">P. protecta</taxonomicName>
in having the bifurcated inner pygofer process and large ventral projection. But it can be easily distinguished by the following morphological features: apex of style reaching distal 
<number box="[324,334,1301,1325]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[345,359,1301,1325]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="3.0">3</number>
of subgenital plate; ventral margin of pygofer roundly sinuate; aedeagal shaft weakly recurved dorsad and widened near base. In many localities including the 
<typeStatus box="[865,913,1338,1362]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">type</typeStatus>
locality, the pygofer process of the male genitalia is usually slender (
<figureCitation box="[423,507,1373,1397]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 27" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1887,1910]" captionTargetBox="[217,1363,188,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[213,1373,175,1867]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 27. Pagaronia totoumiensis sp. nov., Ψ abdominal terminalia (16 – 17) and ɗ genitalia (18 – 27). — 16, 7 th abdominal sternum; 17, Ψ pygofer in lateral view; 18, ɗ pygofer in lateral view; 19 – 20, left inner pygofer process; 21, left subgenital plate; 22, apical part of left style; 23, aedeagus in lateral view; 24, shaft in dorsal view; 25, ventral projection in caudal view; 26 – 27, apical part of shaft (26) and ventral projection (27) in apical view. Scales; 0.3 mm (16 – 21, 23 – 25), 0.1 mm (22) and 0.05 mm (26, 27)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211834/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[477,507,1373,1397]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
), but it is somewhat broadened in the specimens from Sakurachô-ôi, Hamamatsu City (
<figureCitation box="[214,299,1409,1433]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 27" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1887,1910]" captionTargetBox="[217,1363,188,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[213,1373,175,1867]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 27. Pagaronia totoumiensis sp. nov., Ψ abdominal terminalia (16 – 17) and ɗ genitalia (18 – 27). — 16, 7 th abdominal sternum; 17, Ψ pygofer in lateral view; 18, ɗ pygofer in lateral view; 19 – 20, left inner pygofer process; 21, left subgenital plate; 22, apical part of left style; 23, aedeagus in lateral view; 24, shaft in dorsal view; 25, ventral projection in caudal view; 26 – 27, apical part of shaft (26) and ventral projection (27) in apical view. Scales; 0.3 mm (16 – 21, 23 – 25), 0.1 mm (22) and 0.05 mm (26, 27)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211834/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[267,299,1409,1433]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
). The species name is based on the ancient district name around the 
<typeStatus box="[1063,1111,1410,1434]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">type</typeStatus>
locality, “Tô-tou-mi”.
</paragraph>
